  "prompt": "What is the proper way to use RSVP out of the following?",
  "response": "Okay, let's break down the proper use of \"RSVP.\"\n\n**What RSVP Stands For**\n\nRSVP stands for the French phrase \"R\u00e9pondez s'il vous pla\u00eet,\" which translates to \"Please reply.\"\n\n**How to Use RSVP Correctly**\n\nThe key is to remember that **RSVP is an instruction, not a request for information.**\n\nHere's the breakdown:\n\n*   **On an Invitation:**  You include \"RSVP\" followed by instructions on how the person should respond.  This usually includes:\n    *   **A Date:** A deadline by which the person needs to reply.\n    *   **A Method:** How they should reply (e.g., phone number, email address, website).\n\n*   **Responding to an RSVP:** You must reply with your attendance intentions, whether you can attend or not.\n\n**Examples of Correct Usage**\n\n*   **On an Invitation:**\n\n    *   \"RSVP by July 15th to events@example.com\"\n    *   \"RSVP to Sarah at 555-123-4567 by June 1st.\"\n    *   \"Please RSVP online at [website address] by October 20th.\"\n\n*   **Responding to an Invitation (Example):**\n\n    *   If the invitation said \"RSVP to events@example.com by July 15th,\" you would send an email to that address saying something like:\n        *   \"Subject: RSVP - [Your Name] - [Event Name]\"\n        *   \"Dear [Host Name],\n           Thank you for the invitation to [Event Name].  I am delighted to accept and will be attending.\n           Sincerely,\n           [Your Name]\"\n        *   **OR**\n        *   \"Subject: RSVP - [Your Name] - [Event Name]\"\n        *   \"Dear [Host Name],\n           Thank you for the invitation to [Event Name].  Unfortunately, I will be unable to attend due to [brief reason, optional].\n           Sincerely,\n           [Your Name]\"\n\n**Common Mistakes to Avoid**\n\n*   **\"Please RSVP\":** This is redundant.  RSVP *already* means \"Please reply.\"  Just use \"RSVP.\"\n*   **Asking for More Information After RSVPing:** After RSVPing, do not follow up asking for additional details that were already provided on the invitation. The host already expects you.\n\n**In Summary**\n\nUse \"RSVP\" on an invitation to *tell* people to respond and *how* to respond.  When you receive an invitation with \"RSVP\" instructions, *follow* those instructions and reply by the deadline.\n",
